  "local_port": 53708,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "Which country offers the best MBA program with affordable fees and cost of living?",
  "response": "Several countries are known for offering high-quality MBA programs with relatively affordable tuition fees and cost of living. Here are some of the top options:\n\n1. **Germany**: \n   - **Why Germany?**: Many universities in Germany offer MBA programs with low or no tuition fees, even for international students, especially at public universities. Living costs are also moderate compared to other Western European countries or North America.\n   - **Top Schools**: Mannheim Business School, WHU - Otto Beisheim School of Management, HHL Leipzig Graduate School of Management.\n   - **Cost of Living**: \u20ac800\u2013\u20ac1,200 per month.\n   - **Tuition Fees**: \u20ac5,000\u2013\u20ac30,000 per year (private schools), often free or minimal at public universities.\n\n2. **Canada**:\n   - **Why Canada?**: Canadian MBA programs are globally recognized, and the country offers a high quality of life with relatively affordable tuition compared to the U.S. Additionally, Canada has a welcoming immigration policy for international students.\n   - **Top Schools**: University of Toronto (Rotman), McGill University (Desautels), University of British Columbia (Sauder).\n   - **Cost of Living**: CAD 1,000\u2013CAD 1,500 per month.\n   - **Tuition Fees**: CAD 30,000\u2013CAD 60,000 per year.\n\n3. **Spain**:\n   - **Why Spain?**: Spain offers prestigious MBA programs with lower tuition fees compared to U.S. or UK schools. The cost of living is also reasonable, especially in smaller cities.\n   - **Top Schools**: IESE Business School, IE Business School, ESADE Business School.\n   - **Cost of Living**: \u20ac700\u2013\u20ac1,200 per month.\n   - **Tuition Fees**: \u20ac30,000\u2013\u20ac70,000 per year.\n\n4. **India**:\n   - **Why India?**: India is one of the most affordable countries for pursuing an MBA, with top-tier programs at a fraction of the cost of Western institutions. The cost of living is also very low.\n   - **Top Schools**: Indian Institutes of Management (IIMs), Indian School of Business (ISB).\n   - **Cost of Living**: \u20b910,000\u2013\u20b920,000 per month.\n   - **Tuition Fees**: \u20b910 lakh\u2013\u20b925 lakh for the entire program.\n\n5. **Taiwan**:\n   - **Why Taiwan?**: Taiwan offers high-quality MBA programs with low tuition fees and a very affordable cost of living. It\u2019s a great option for students looking to study in Asia.\n   - **Top Schools**: National Taiwan University (NTU), National Chengchi University (NCCU).\n   - **Cost of Living**: NT$10,000\u2013NT$15,000 per month.\n   - **Tuition Fees**: NT$200,000\u2013NT$400,000 per year.\n\n6. **Mexico**:\n   - **Why Mexico?**: Mexico offers affordable MBA programs with a low cost of living, making it an attractive option for students in Latin America or those looking for a culturally rich experience.\n   - **Top Schools**: IPADE Business School, EGADE Business School.\n   - **Cost of Living**: MXN 8,000\u2013MXN 12,000 per month.\n   - **Tuition Fees**: MXN 200,000\u2013MXN 400,000 per year.\n\nConsiderations When Choosing:\n- **Accreditation**: Ensure the program is accredited by recognized bodies like AACSB, EQUIS, or AMBA.\n- **Career Opportunities**: Look for schools with strong alumni networks and career services.\n- **Language**: Consider if the program is taught in English or if you\u2019ll need to learn the local language.\n- **Location**: Think about your preferred living environment and cultural fit.\n\nUltimately, the \"best\" country depends on your personal goals, budget, and career aspirations.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
